<P>THE JUST LIMITATION OF SLAVERY IN THE LAWS OF GOD, COMPARED WITH The unbounded Claims of the AFRICAN TRADERS and BRITISH AMERICAN SLAVEHOLDERS.</P>
<P>BY GRANVILLE SHARP.</P>
<P>With a copious APPENDIX: CONTAINING,</P>
<P>An An&s;wer to the Rev. Mr. Thomp&s;on's Tract in favour of the <HI>African Slave Trade.</HI>&mdash;Letters con|cerning <HI>the lineal De&s;cent of the Negroes</HI> from the Sons of HAM.&mdash;The Spani&s;h Regulations for the gradual Enfranchi&s;ement of Slaves.&mdash;A Propo&s;al on the &s;ame Principles for the gradual Enfran|chi&s;ement of Slaves in <HI>America.</HI>&mdash;Reports of De|terminations in the &s;everal COURTS OF LAW AGAINST SLAVERY, &amp;c.</P>
<Q>&mdash;Take away your Exactions from my People, SAITH THE LORD GOD!
<BIBL>Ezekiel xlv. 9.</BIBL></Q>
